CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 14, 1945, pg. 8, reads: "Sponsored Successful Affair - The presentation of 'Mannequins of '45,' which was one of the most successful events of its kind, was sponsored by the Toujour Fideles, a club of young women in St. James AME Church. The event took place at May - Stern Auditorium. In the photo are (left to right), front row: Mrs. Hubert Robinson, Miss Jane Bailey, Mrs. Cleo B. Jones, Mrs. Gladys Howell, Mrs. Jacqueline Primas, Miss Jean McCoy, Mrs. Julia Gaines, the Rev. Hubert N. Robinson. Second row: Mrs. Christine Williams, Miss Marcella Palmer, Miss Dorothy Harris, Mrs. Fredericka Fulwylie, Mrs. Dolores Taylor and Miss Elnora Sneed. Members of the club not in the photo are: Mmes. Isabella K. Stewart, Margaret Terry, Helen Cyrus and Thelma Walker. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Toujour Fideles Club members, first row from left: Mrs. Hubert Robinson, Jane Bailey (Shelton), Cleo Blakney Jones, Gladys Howell, Jacqueline Primas, Jean McCoy, Julia Hurst Gaines, Rev. Hubert N. Robinson; second row: Christine Williams, Marcella Palmer, Dorothy Harris, Fredericka Fulwylie, Dolores Taylor and Elnora Sneed posed for fashion show in May - Sterns department store
